CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1774383073
OL,3,CKent MP calls for #22m South East
OL,4,CWater fine to be waived to force
OL,5,Cinvestment
OL,7,FThe MP has written to water regular
OL,8,FOfwat arguing that replacing the fine
OL,9,Fwith enforced investment could
OL,10,F"dramatically improve the resilience
OL,11,Fof the Pembury Water Treatment Works",
OL,12,Fwhich he describes as a "single point
OL,13,Fof failure" in the Tunbridge Wells
OL,14,Fwater network.
OL,16,FThe Liberal Democrat politician has
OL,17,Fworked with industry experts to draw
OL,18,Fup his own water resilience plan for
OL,19,Fthe local area, estimated to cost
OL,20,Fbetween #19.5m and #69.3m.
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@eO]tD@YOUuD@KO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
